<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Sadia Concordia raised.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Sadia Concordia raised.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Robert Fleming analyst Mark de Speville has raised his rating for Brazilian food group Sadia Concordia SA to buy from hold.</p>
<p>-- In a May 22 report, de Speville cited Sadia's cost-cutting efforts, higher gross margin, better capacity utilization and a higher value-added sales mix for the upgrade.</p>
<p>-- &quot;Given our expectation of a recovery in earnings as well as lower volatility, we are upgrading Sadia from hold to buy,&quot; he wrote.</p>
<p>-- Sadia's preferred shares closed Thursday at 0.94 real in Sao Paulo.</p>
<p>((--Ian Simpson, Wall Street desk, (212) 859-1879))</p>
